<span class="s1">&lt;/tbody&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/table&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draw several simple shapes to a surface. These functions will work for</span>
<span class="s0">rendering to any format of surface.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Most of the functions take a width argument to represent the size of stroke</span>
<span class="s0">(thickness) around the edge of the shape. If a width of 0 is passed the shape</span>
<span class="s0">will be filled (solid).</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">All the drawing functions respect the clip area for the surface and will be</span>
<span class="s0">constrained to that area. The functions return a rectangle representing the</span>
<span class="s0">bounding area of changed pixels. This bounding rectangle is the 'minimum'</span>
<span class="s0">bounding box that encloses the affected area.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">All the drawing functions accept a color argument that can be one of the</span>
<span class="s0">following formats:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div&gt;&lt;ul </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;simple&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">a </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;color.html#pygame.Color&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.Color</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame object for color representations</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">object</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">an </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(RGB)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">triplet (tuple/list)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">an </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(RGBA)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">quadruplet (tuple/list)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">an integer value that has been mapped to the surface's pixel format</span>
<span class="s0">(see </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;surface.html#pygame.Surface.map_rgb&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.Surface.map_rgb()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">convert a color into a mapped color value</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">and </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;surface.html#pygame.Surface.unmap_rgb&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.Surface.unmap_rgb()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">convert a mapped integer color value into a Color</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/ul&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A color's alpha value will be written directly into the surface (if the</span>
<span class="s0">surface contains pixel alphas), but the draw function will not draw</span>
<span class="s0">transparently.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">These functions temporarily lock the surface they are operating on. Many</span>
<span class="s0">sequential drawing calls can be sped up by locking and unlocking the surface</span>
<span class="s0">object around the draw calls (see </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;surface.html#pygame.Surface.lock&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.Surface.lock()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">lock the Surface memory for pixel access</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">and</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;surface.html#pygame.Surface.unlock&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.Surface.unlock()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">unlock the Surface memory from pixel access</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">).</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition note&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">See the </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;gfxdraw.html#module-pygame.gfxdraw&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-mod docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.gfxdraw</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame module for drawing shapes</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">module for alternative draw methods.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s0">Nothing is drawn when the radius is 0 (a pixel at the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">center</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">coordinates</span>
<span class="s0">used to be drawn when the radius equaled 0).</span>
<span class="s0">Floats, and Vector2 are accepted for the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">center</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">param.</span>
<span class="s0">The drawing algorithm was improved to look more like a circle.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draws an elliptical arc on the given surface.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The two angle arguments are given in radians and indicate the start and stop</span>
<span class="s0">positions of the arc. The arc is drawn in a counterclockwise direction from</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">line(surface, color, start_pos, end_pos) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">line(surface, color, start_pos, end_pos, width=1) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draws a straight line on the given surface. There are no endcaps. For thick</span>
<span class="s0">lines the ends are squared off.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition note&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition-title&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Note</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">When using </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">width</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">values </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt;</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, lines will grow as follows.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">For odd </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">width</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">values, the thickness of each line grows with the</span>
<span class="s0">original line being in the center.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">For even </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">width</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">values, the thickness of each line grows with the</span>
<span class="s0">original line being offset from the center (as there is no exact</span>
<span class="s0">center line drawn). As a result, lines with a slope </span><span class="s4">&amp;lt; </span><span class="s0">1</span>
<span class="s0">(horizontal-ish) will have 1 more pixel of thickness below the</span>
<span class="s0">original line (in the y direction). Lines with a slope </span><span class="s4">&amp;gt;</span><span class="s0">= 1</span>
<span class="s0">(vertical-ish) will have 1 more pixel of thickness to the right of</span>
<span class="s0">the original line (in the x direction).</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">draw multiple contiguous straight line segments</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">lines(surface, color, closed, points) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">lines(surface, color, closed, points, width=1) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draws a sequence of contiguous straight lines on the given surface. There are</span>
<span class="s0">no endcaps or miter joints. For thick lines the ends are squared off.</span>
<span class="s0">Drawing thick lines with sharp corners can have undesired looking results.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig sig-object py title&quot; </span><span class="s2">id</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.draw.aaline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-prename descclassname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.draw.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-name descname&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">aaline</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;sig-paren&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;headerlink&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.draw.aaline&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;Permalink to this definition&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">¶</span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">draw a straight antialiased line</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">aaline(surface, color, start_pos, end_pos) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">aaline(surface, color, start_pos, end_pos, blend=1) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Rect</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Draws a straight antialiased line on the given surface.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">The line has a thickness of one pixel and the endpoints have a height and</span>
<span class="s0">width of one pixel each.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dl&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt&gt;</span><span class="s0">The way a line and its endpoints are drawn:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If both endpoints are equal, only a single pixel is drawn (after</span>
<span class="s0">rounding floats to nearest integer).</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Otherwise if the line is not steep (i.e. if the length along the x-axis</span>
<span class="s0">is greater than the height along the y-axis):</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">For each endpoint:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">x</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, the endpoint's x-coordinate, is a whole number find</span>
<span class="s0">which pixels would be covered by it and draw them.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Otherwise:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Calculate the position of the nearest point with a whole number</span>
<span class="s0">for its x-coordinate, when extending the line past the</span>
<span class="s0">endpoint.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Find which pixels would be covered and how much by that point.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If the endpoint is the left one, multiply the coverage by (1 -</span>
<span class="s0">the decimal part of </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">x</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">).</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Otherwise multiply the coverage by the decimal part of </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">x</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Then draw those pixels.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dl&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">e.g.:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">The left endpoint of the line </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">((1,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1.3),</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(5,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">3))</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">would</span>
<span class="s0">cover 70% of the pixel </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(1,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and 30% of the pixel</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(1,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">2)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">while the right one would cover 100% of the</span>
<span class="s0">pixel </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(5,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">3)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">The left endpoint of the line </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">((1.2,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1.4),</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(4.6,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">3.1))</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span>
<span class="s0">would cover 56% </span><span class="s1">&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">(i.e. 0.8 * 70%)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt; </span><span class="s0">of the pixel </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(1,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span>
<span class="s0">and 24% </span><span class="s1">&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">(i.e. 0.8 * 30%)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt; </span><span class="s0">of the pixel </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(1,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">2)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">while</span>
<span class="s0">the right one would cover 42% </span><span class="s1">&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">(i.e. 0.6 * 70%)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt; </span><span class="s0">of the</span>
<span class="s0">pixel </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(5,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">3)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and 18% </span><span class="s1">&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">(i.e. 0.6 * 30%)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt; </span><span class="s0">of the pixel</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(5,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">4)</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">while the right</span><span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dl&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Then for each point between the endpoints, along the line, whose</span>
<span class="s0">x-coordinate is a whole number:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;blockquote&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Find which pixels would be covered and how much by that point and</span>
<span class="s0">draw them.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dl&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">e.g.:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">The points along the line </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">((1,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">1),</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">(4,</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">2.5))</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">would be</span>
